      <h2>How Cannabis Social Clubs Work in Madrid</h2>

      <p>Cannabis social clubs (CSCs) in Madrid operate as private, non-profit associations under Spanish law. They are not coffee shops, dispensaries, or retail stores. The model is fundamentally different from anything in Amsterdam, California, or Thailand — and misunderstanding this causes most tourist problems.</p>

      <h3>The Legal Structure</h3>
      <p>Each club registers as an <em>asociacion</em> (association) under the Spanish Organic Law on Associations. Members pool resources to collectively cultivate cannabis for shared personal use. No profit is generated — the money you pay inside is technically a "contribution" to the association, not a purchase. This legal framework is what keeps the clubs operating within Spain's constitutional privacy protections.</p>

      <h3>What Happens Inside</h3>
      <p>Legitimate Madrid cannabis clubs typically feature a reception/check-in area where your membership card is verified, a lounge with seating, tables, and often a bar serving non-alcoholic drinks and snacks, a dispensing counter where members select products and make their contributions, and sometimes entertainment like pool tables, PlayStation consoles, board games, or occasional live music.</p>

      <p>The atmosphere varies dramatically between clubs. Some feel like upscale cocktail lounges with dim lighting and curated playlists. Others are more casual — think neighborhood bar with a Spanish football match on TV. A few cater specifically to international tourists with English-speaking staff and menus.</p>

      <h3>Product Quality vs. Street</h3>
      <p>The quality difference between club products and street-purchased cannabis is significant. Clubs source from regulated cultivation operations, test for contaminants, and label strains accurately. Street cannabis in Madrid is frequently adulterated — we have documented cases of flower sprayed with synthetic cannabinoids, hash cut with henna or tire rubber, and vape cartridges filled with vitamin E acetate. The health risk alone makes clubs the only rational choice.</p>

      <p class="section__deep-link"><a href="/cannabis-clubs-madrid/">Full guide to cannabis clubs: what is inside, etiquette, product menus, and how to choose the right club →</a></p>
