    <!-- 7. What to Expect -->
    <section id="what-to-expect" class="section">
      <h2>What to Expect Inside a Madrid Cannabis Club</h2>

      <p>If you have never been to a cannabis social club before, here is exactly what the experience looks like from the moment you walk in.</p>

      <h3>Arrival &amp; Check-In</h3>
      <p>You ring a doorbell or intercom (most clubs have unmarked entrances — this is intentional, not suspicious). Staff will ask for your membership card or invitation link. First-time visitors go through the registration process at the reception desk. This takes 10-20 minutes depending on how busy the club is.</p>

      <h3>Browsing the Menu</h3>
      <p>Once inside, you approach the dispensing counter. Most clubs display their current menu on a board, screen, or printed sheet. Menus typically list 4-12 flower strains, 2-6 hash varieties, pre-rolls, and sometimes edibles or concentrates. Staff can help you choose based on your preferences — do not hesitate to ask for recommendations if you are unfamiliar with the products.</p>

      <h3>Making Your Contribution</h3>
      <p>You select your products and make your financial contribution. Most clubs are <strong>cash only</strong> — bring euros. A few larger clubs have started accepting card payments in 2026, but do not count on it. The contribution covers your share of the collective cultivation costs.</p>

      <h3>The Lounge Experience</h3>
      <p>Find a seat in the lounge area and consume at your pace. Most clubs provide rolling papers, tips, grinders, and sometimes bongs or vaporizers for on-site use. You can order drinks (non-alcoholic in most clubs, though some serve beer and wine) and snacks. Stay as long as you like — there is no time pressure.</p>

      <h3>Etiquette Rules</h3>
      <ul class="pillar-list">
        <li>Do not take photos or videos inside (this is a strict rule at every legitimate club)</li>
        <li>Do not bring outside cannabis into the club</li>
        <li>Do not share your membership card with non-members</li>
        <li>Keep noise levels reasonable — other members are there to relax too</li>
        <li>Tip staff if service is good (not required but appreciated)</li>
        <li>Do not attempt to take product out of the club</li>
      </ul>

